commit.message: Merge branch 'fix-bsd-build' of https://github.com/abs0/siege into abs0-fix-bsd-build
Merge branch 'tread-typo' of https://github.com/abs0/siege into abs0-tread-typo

Add configure check for getaddrinfo()

Extend use of getaddrinfo() from defined(__GLIBC__) to
any system where configure can find it.

Avoids falling back to (usually non thread-safe) gethostbyname()
on BSD systems, which does not end well when concurrency > 1

Fix build on NetBSD, FreeBSD, OpenBSD & DragonFlyBSD

On *BSD systems <signal.h> must be included to use signal constants.

(It most likely could be unconditionally included on all systems)
Fix segmentation fault in cookie functions
Added siege attribute persistent to persist -g cks
